(42, 2, 52, 44, 7, 9, 10, 'favour with God and man', 'Connection of Favor and Wisdom', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''favour'' and ''wisdom'' in the lives of Jesus and Joseph. Jesus ''increased in favour with God and man,'' while Joseph was given ''favour and wisdom in the sight of Pharaoh.''', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 1, 1, 49, 10, 10, NULL, 'Authority and Governance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of governance and authority. In Luke 3:1, the mention of rulers sets the stage for the arrival of a significant figure, while Genesis 49:10 speaks of the enduring authority of Judah until Shiloh comes, suggesting a transition in leadership.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 1, 40, 27, 2, 2, 'Pontius Pilate being governor', 'Connection between Pilate references', 'Both passages emphasize Pontius Pilate''s role as governor. Luke introduces Pilate in the context of leadership, while Matthew describes his involvement in Jesus'' trial.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 1, 42, 2, 1, 1, 'Cesar', 'Connection of Roman Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Cesar in governance. The mention of Cesar Augustus in Luke 2:1 and Tiberius Cesar in Luke 3:1 highlights the continuity of Roman political authority during the time of Jesus'' birth and ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 1, 42, 9, 7, 7, 'Herod being tetrarch of Galilee', 'Herod''s Role in Both Passages', 'Both passages emphasize Herod being tetrarch, linking his authority to the events surrounding John the Baptist. The mention of Herod in both contexts highlights his involvement in the narrative of Jesus and John.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 1, 44, 4, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Political Figures', 'Both passages emphasize the roles of Herod and Pontius Pilate in relation to Jesus. This connection highlights their political authority during significant events in Jesus'' life and ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 1, 40, 14, 1, 1, 'Herod being tetrarch of Galilee', 'Herod''s Role in Jesus'' Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize Herod''s position as tetrarch, linking him to the events surrounding Jesus'' fame. This connection highlights the political context in which Jesus'' ministry occurred.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 1, 41, 6, 17, 17, 'Herod being tetrarch of Galilee', 'Herod''s Role in Both Passages', 'This connection highlights Herod''s involvement in both passages. In Luke, Herod is identified as tetrarch of Galilee, while in Mark, he plays a significant role in the imprisonment of John due to his marriage to Philip''s wife.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 2, 44, 4, 6, 6, 'Annas and Caiaphas being the high priests', 'Connection of High Priests', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Annas and Caiaphas as high priests. This connection highlights their continued influence in the early ministry of John and the early church.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 2, 32, 1, 1, 1, 'the word of God came', 'Divine Communication to Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''the word of God came'' to prophets, highlighting a divine call to deliver messages. This connection illustrates a pattern of God speaking to chosen individuals for prophetic missions.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 2, 42, 1, 80, 80, NULL, 'John''s Wilderness Preparation', 'Both passages emphasize John''s time in the wilderness, highlighting his growth and preparation for his role in revealing God''s word to Israel. This connection illustrates the significance of his spiritual development before his ministry begins.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 2, 43, 18, 24, 24, 'Annas and Caiaphas being the high priests', 'Connection between Annas and Caiaphas', 'Both passages emphasize the roles of Annas and Caiaphas in the high priesthood. The first passage introduces them as high priests, while the second describes Annas sending Jesus to Caiaphas, highlighting their interconnected authority.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 2, 40, 26, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of High Priests', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Caiaphas as a high priest. In Luke, the mention of Annas and Caiaphas sets the religious leadership context, while Matthew highlights Caiaphas''s involvement in the assembly against Jesus.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 2, 23, 40, 3, 3, 'in the wilderness', 'Connection of Wilderness Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of the wilderness as a setting for divine communication and preparation. Both passages emphasize the call to prepare for the Lord''s coming in the wilderness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 2, 33, 1, 1, 1, 'the word of God came', 'Connection of Divine Communication', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''the word of God came'' to signify divine revelation. This connection highlights the continuity of God''s communication to His prophets across different eras.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 3, 42, 1, 77, 77, 'remission of sins', 'Remission of Sins Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''remission of sins.'' Luke 3:3 speaks of baptism for the remission of sins, while Luke 1:77 highlights knowledge of salvation through the remission of sins.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 3, 40, 3, 5, 6, 'baptism of repentance for the remission of sins', 'Baptism and Confession of Sins', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism and repentance present in both passages. Luke mentions ''the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins,'' while Matthew describes people being baptized and ''confessing their sins.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 3, 44, 13, 24, 24, 'baptism of repentance', 'Baptism of Repentance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the ''baptism of repentance'' as a key message. This connection highlights the continuity of John''s preaching in relation to the coming of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 3, 40, 3, 11, 11, 'baptism of repentance for the remission of sins', 'Baptism and Repentance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize baptism as a means of repentance. Luke mentions ''the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins,'' while Matthew refers to baptism ''unto repentance.'' This connection highlights the significance of baptism in the context of repentance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 3, 43, 1, 31, 33, 'baptism of repentance for the remission of sins', 'Baptism and Manifestation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism for repentance in both passages. Luke 3:3 mentions ''baptism of repentance for the remission of sins,'' while John 1:31 emphasizes John''s role in baptizing to reveal Jesus, who will baptize with the Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 3, 43, 3, 26, 26, 'baptism of repentance', 'Connection of Baptism and Witness', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism as both passages discuss the act of baptizing and its significance. Luke 3:3 mentions the baptism of repentance, while John 3:26 refers to the one who baptizes, indicating a continuity in the practice and its importance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 3, 44, 19, 4, 4, 'baptism of repentance', 'Baptism of Repentance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the ''baptism of repentance'' as a significant act. Luke describes John the Baptist''s ministry, while Paul references it to highlight the need for belief in Christ Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 4, 23, 40, 3, 5, 'Prepare ye the way of the Lord', 'Connection of Prophetic Voice', 'Both passages emphasize the call to prepare the way for the Lord. The phrase ''Prepare ye the way of the Lord'' directly links the prophetic message in Isaiah to the announcement in Luke.', 'quotation', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 4, 43, 1, 23, 23, 'The voice of one crying in the wilderness', 'Connection of Prophetic Voice', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a voice in the wilderness calling for preparation for the Lord. This connection highlights the fulfillment of Isaiah''s prophecy as John identifies himself with that voice.', 'prophecy', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
